import re

def valid_filename(filename):
    pattern = re.compile("[a-zA-Z _\-]+")
    if pattern.fullmatch(filename):
        return True
    else:
        return False

# Test cases

print(valid_filename("123_Testing")) # True

Non-examples:

def evaluate_currency(value):
    pattern = r'^\d{1,5}(\.\d{1,2})?$'
    if re.match(pattern, value):
        return True
    else:
        return False

def validate_hexadecimal(input_string):
    pattern = re.compile(r'^([0-9A-Fa-f]{2}[:-]){5}([0-9A-Fa-f]{2})$')
    if len(input_string) < 17 or len(input_string) > 19:
        return False
    if not pattern.match(input_string):
        return False
    return True
